---
import ArticleLayout from '../../layouts/ArticleLayout.astro';

const locale = 'en';
---

<ArticleLayout
  title="Changelog"
  description="Release history for WorthCalc's free money-decision calculators."
  locale={locale}
  updated="2026-07-19"
  alternateLocales={['en', 'zh', 'es', 'fr', 'de']}
>
  <h2>v1.2.0 - Native-language trust and editorial shell</h2>
  <p><time datetime="2026-07-19">July 19, 2026</time></p>
  <p>
    Added market-written Spanish, French, and German pages for About, Privacy,
    Terms, Contact, Disclaimer, and this changelog. Each published family now
    has a canonical URL, six hreflang signals including x-default, breadcrumb
    structured data, sitemap coverage, a substantive-content floor, and a
    375-pixel browser check. Thin existing English and Traditional Chinese
    trust pages were expanded when the same audit exposed a gap.
  </p>
  <h2>v1.1.0 - 29 decision topics in five languages</h2>
  <p><time datetime="2026-07-18">July 18–19, 2026</time></p>
  <p>
    Completed 29 editorial topics in English, Traditional Chinese, Spanish,
    French, and German: 145 structured variants. These are not bulk
    translations. Market terms, contracts, authorities, costs, examples, and
    source choices are written for each audience. Every guide includes a
    formula, assumptions, worked example, limitations, FAQ, and sources; 35
    interactive decision calculators are embedded across the library.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Financing, BNPL, upfront fees, and real annual borrowing cost.</li>
    <li>Subscriptions, memberships, cards, rewards, and spending caps.</li>
    <li>Housing, vehicles, commuting, remote work, and the value of time.</li>
    <li>Repair, warranties, energy, consumption, food, wages, and inflation.</li>
  </ul>
  <h2>v1.0.0 - WorthCalc launch</h2>
  <p><time datetime="2026-07">July 2026</time></p>
  <p>
    First public release of WorthCalc, with eight free, browser-based
    calculators that answer one question: is it actually worth it?
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Installment True APR Calculator — the real interest rate behind "0%" installment and BNPL plans.</li>
    <li>Subscription Audit Calculator — total subscription cost per month, year, and 5 years.</li>
    <li>Costco Membership Calculator — break-even spend for Gold Star and Executive tiers.</li>
    <li>EV vs Gas Car TCO Calculator — total cost of ownership and break-even year.</li>
    <li>Rent vs Buy Calculator — mortgage, appreciation, and invested down payment vs. renting.</li>
    <li>Commute Cost Calculator — car, transit, rideshare, and bike compared side by side.</li>
    <li>Latte Factor Calculator — what a daily habit costs, and its future value if invested.</li>
    <li>Cashback Break-even Calculator — annual-fee card vs. a no-fee 1% baseline.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Also included at launch: bilingual English and Traditional Chinese pages,
    four supporting guides on installments, subscriptions, warehouse-club math,
    and rent vs. buy, plus a fully client-side privacy model — no calculator
    input ever leaves your browser.
  </p>
  <h2>How to read this log</h2>
  <p>
    A version groups a visible capability. A focused correction may update a
    formula, source, accessibility behavior, review date, or metadata without
    changing a calculator's purpose. Traffic and revenue figures are never
    inserted here unless they come from documented measurement. Report a
    regression with the URL, inputs, displayed result, and expected result.
  </p>
</ArticleLayout>
